FT  23 JUN 92 / UK Company News: Polar slips to Pounds 451,000
Polar, the USM-quoted marketer and distributor of electronic components,
returned profits of Pounds 451,000 pre-tax on sales of Pounds 8.3m for the
six months ended March 31.
The figures compare with Pounds 482,000 and Pounds 7.7m respectively for the
same period a year ago. Earnings worked through at 3.7p (4p) and the interim
dividend is a same-again 2p.
The directors anticipate a full-year result similar to 1990-91's Pounds
917,000. However, they pointed out that the order book indicated that the
next financial year 'should show a resumption of growth.'
